==English==
===Verb===
'''[[speak]] [[for]]'''
# To [[speak]] on somebody's [[behalf]].
#:''I think I '''speak for''' the whole group when I say that we're glad you came.''
#{{idiom}} To [[claim]], [[reserve]], or [[occupy]].
#:''Be sure to '''speak for''' a seat early, if you plan to attend.''

